39
00:02:39,514 --> 00:02:42,980
We think of 1978 as the crucial year.

40
00:02:42,980 --> 00:02:46,810
But in fact, the Eighth Party Congress, in 1956,

41
00:02:46,810 --> 00:02:51,770
already displayed a vision of trying to modernize China.

42
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:54,965
They were building a 12 year scientific plan.

43
00:02:54,965 --> 00:02:57,110
They had an economic plan.

44
00:02:57,110 --> 00:03:02,300
The Soviet Union was helping introduce all kinds of factories.

45
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:06,050
And they were on the way to beginning modernization.

46
00:03:06,050 --> 00:03:07,950
And he led that process.

47
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:11,880
But Deng was one who knew that you needed a leader.

48
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:17,260
And he believed that the job of people down below was to listen to the leader

49
00:03:17,260 --> 00:03:18,040
and carry out.

50
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,530
You needed discipline.

51
00:03:19,530 --> 00:03:21,560
And Mao was in charge.

52
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,930
And if Mao wanted something, he would do it.

53
00:03:23,930 --> 00:03:29,020
In 1957, he destroyed a lot of lives of intellectuals

54
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:33,080
in the campaign known as the Anti-Rightist Campaign.

55
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:36,340
Over 550,000 people were attacked.

56
00:03:36,340 --> 00:03:40,740
He was honest later in admitting that he had been responsible,

57
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:44,050
also, for the Great Leap Forward in some of those eras.

58
00:03:44,050 --> 00:03:49,170
But in about 1961, '62, he began to depart from Mao.

59
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:55,800
Mao wanted to continue pushing revolution, class struggle.

60
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:59,110
Deng was said by Mao to be sitting in the background,

61
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:00,610
not listening to his speech.

62
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:04,410
They knew that if he was up close, he would have to do what Mao said.

63
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:08,070
But if he sat a little distance, he would

64
00:04:08,070 --> 00:04:10,100
be able to have little degree of freedom,

65
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:13,010
didn't report to Mao anymore than he had to

66
00:04:13,010 --> 00:04:15,740
so he could begin to take realistic steps.

67
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,060
He was on the front line.

68
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:19,940
Mao was the philosopher, the theorist behind.

69
00:04:19,940 --> 00:04:24,180
And Deng was a man who was on target in terms

70
